cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer vision tasks, specifically focusing on the incorporation of location information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for feature learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of location information for improving segmentation and parsing, which are tasks related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of distance transforms, which are commonly used in neural networks for image processing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses experiments with salient object segmentation, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM).
